name: HTML
title: HTML-5
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced HTML-5.
description: HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is a standard markup language for web page creation. It allows the creation and structure of sections, paragraphs, and links using HTML elements (the building blocks of a web page) such as tags and attributes.

name: CSS
title: CSS-3
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced CSS-3.
description: CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) allows you to create great-looking web pages, but how does it work under the hood? This article explains what CSS is with a simple syntax example and also covers some key terms about the language.

name: BootStrap
title: BootStrap
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced BootStrap.
description: Bootstrap is a free and open-source web development framework. It’s designed to ease the web development process of responsive, mobile-first websites by providing a collection of syntax for template designs.

name: TailWind
title: TailWind CSS
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced TailWind CSs.
description: Tailwind is a utility-first CSS framework. In contrast to other CSS frameworks like Bootstrap or Materialize CSS it doesn’t come with predefined components. Instead Tailwind CSS operates on a lower level and provides you with a set of CSS helper classes. By using this classes you can rapidly create custom design with ease. Tailwind CSS is not opinionated and let’s you create you own unique design.

name: Git & GitHub
title: Git & GitHub
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced Git & GitHub.

name: JavaScript
title: JavaScript
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced JavaScript.
description: JavaScript is a scripting or programming language that allows you to implement complex features on web pages — every time a web page does more than just sit there and display static information for you to look at — displaying timely content updates, interactive maps, animated 2D/3D graphics, scrolling video jukeboxes, etc. — you can bet that JavaScript is probably involved. It is the third layer of the layer cake of standard web technologies, two of which (HTML and CSS) we have covered in much more detail in other parts of the Learning Area.

name: ES6
title: ES-6
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced EcmaScript-6.
description: ES6 refers to version 6 of the ECMA Script programming language. ECMA Script is the standardized name for JavaScript, and version 6 is the next version after version 5, which was released in 2011. It is a major enhancement to the JavaScript language, and adds many more features intended to make large-scale software development easier.

name: React JS
title: React JS
detail: This is a course about basic to advanced React Js.
description: React makes it painless to create interactive UIs. Design simple views for each state in your application, and React will efficiently update and render just the right components when your data changes.
